WEBVTT

00:02.500 --> 00:03.760
KATARA: <i>Water.</i>

00:04.710 --> 00:05.920
<i>Earth.</i>

00:06.670 --> 00:07.880
<i>Fire.</i>

00:09.010 --> 00:10.220
<i>Air.</i>

00:11.300 --> 00:14.770
<i>Long ago, the four nations
lived together in harmony.</i>

00:15.310 --> 00:18.810
<i>Then, everything changed
when the Fire Nation attacked.</i>

00:19.690 --> 00:22.570
<i>Only the Avatar,
master of all four elements,</i>

00:22.650 --> 00:23.730
<i>could stop them.</i>

00:23.820 --> 00:26.740
<i>But when the world needed him most,
he vanished.</i>

00:27.110 --> 00:28.360
<i>100 years passed,</i>

00:28.450 --> 00:30.990
<i>and my brother and I
discovered the new Avatar,</i>

00:31.070 --> 00:32.580
<i>an airbender named Aang.</i>

00:33.030 --> 00:35.080
<i>And although
his airbending skills are great</i>

00:35.160 --> 00:37.790
<i>he has a lot to learn
before he's ready to save anyone.</i>

00:37.870 --> 00:39.080
AANG: Oof.

00:39.170 --> 00:41.960
<i>But I believe Aang can save the world.</i>

00:42.290 --> 00:43.960
[ ♪... ]

00:47.970 --> 00:50.470
( MAN READING )

00:50.760 --> 00:51.930
I need you, Zuko.

00:52.010 --> 00:56.770
I've plotted every move of this day,
and the only way we win is together.

00:59.600 --> 01:01.270
We've done it, Zuko.

01:01.350 --> 01:04.070
The Fire Nation has conquered Ba Sing Se.

01:04.150 --> 01:05.440
ZUKO: I betrayed uncle.

01:05.780 --> 01:07.650
AZULA: No, he betrayed you.

01:08.570 --> 01:12.620
When you return home,
father will welcome you as a war hero.

01:12.700 --> 01:14.160
But I don't have the Avatar.

01:14.580 --> 01:16.540
What if father doesn't restore my honor?

01:19.500 --> 01:20.870
[ ♪... ]

01:28.050 --> 01:29.630
( GROANING )

01:35.510 --> 01:36.810
( GRUNTING )

01:41.310 --> 01:42.940
What happened?

01:49.030 --> 01:50.240
Oh, no!

01:57.540 --> 01:59.200
( GRUNTING )

02:01.080 --> 02:02.790
MAN: You hear something?

02:02.870 --> 02:04.420
( GASPING )

02:06.880 --> 02:07.880
MAN: He's awake.

02:08.550 --> 02:09.630
( PANTING )

02:09.710 --> 02:11.260
Stop, wait!

02:12.340 --> 02:14.220
( GRUNTING )

02:18.310 --> 02:19.310
Momo?

02:20.060 --> 02:21.350
( SQUEAKING )

02:24.020 --> 02:26.560
Twinkle-toes, that's got to be you.

02:27.860 --> 02:29.360
Aang, you're awake.

02:29.440 --> 02:30.570
AANG: Are you sure?

02:31.030 --> 02:32.860
I feel like I'm dreaming.

02:32.950 --> 02:33.950
You're not dreaming.

02:34.240 --> 02:35.620
You're finally awake.

02:35.700 --> 02:38.280
Aang, good to see you
back with the living, buddy.

02:39.120 --> 02:40.160
Sokka?

02:40.910 --> 02:42.500
-( SIGHING )
- TOPH: Uh-oh, somebody catch him.

02:42.580 --> 02:43.790
He's gonna...

02:45.290 --> 02:47.590
( GROWLING )

02:56.340 --> 02:57.640
Aren't you cold?

02:58.890 --> 03:00.720
I've got a lot on my mind.

03:01.310 --> 03:03.230
It's been so long.

03:03.310 --> 03:05.440
Over three years since I was home.

03:06.600 --> 03:08.770
I wonder what's changed.

03:08.860 --> 03:10.570
I wonder how I've changed.

03:10.650 --> 03:12.820
( YAWNING ) I just asked if you were cold.

03:12.900 --> 03:15.200
I didn't ask for your whole life story.

03:17.660 --> 03:19.280
Stop worrying.

03:30.040 --> 03:32.170
AANG: Why are we on a Fire Nation ship?

03:32.260 --> 03:34.260
Why is everyone dressed this way?

03:34.340 --> 03:37.300
And why am I the only one
who's completely out of it?

03:37.390 --> 03:38.970
You need to take it easy, ok?

03:39.050 --> 03:41.010
You got hurt pretty bad.

03:42.930 --> 03:44.430
I like your hair.

03:44.520 --> 03:45.890
I have hair?

03:46.770 --> 03:48.150
How long was I out?

03:48.230 --> 03:49.560
A few weeks.

03:49.650 --> 03:50.860
Everything ok?

03:50.940 --> 03:52.110
We're fine, dad.

03:52.440 --> 03:55.400
I'm Hakoda, Katara and Sokka's father.

03:55.490 --> 03:58.070
He knows who you are.
I just called you "dad," didn't I?

03:58.820 --> 04:00.070
I guess you're right.

04:01.530 --> 04:04.000
Nice to officially meet you, Chief Hakoda.

04:04.080 --> 04:05.460
It's an honor to meet you.

04:05.790 --> 04:07.830
Great, great.
Now you guys have finally met,

04:07.920 --> 04:09.880
so would you mind
giving us a little privacy?

04:10.750 --> 04:12.000
Of course.

04:14.340 --> 04:16.380
Are you mad at your dad or something?

04:17.090 --> 04:19.470
What? Not at all. Why would you say that?

04:19.970 --> 04:21.390
( SHRUGS, GROANS )

04:22.470 --> 04:23.770
Maybe we should go upstairs.

04:24.270 --> 04:25.890
You need a healing session.

04:31.270 --> 04:33.520
Tell me where your pain
feels most intense.

04:33.610 --> 04:35.400
( GRUNTING ) A little higher.

04:35.490 --> 04:36.490
( GRUNTS )

04:43.990 --> 04:45.120
Wow.

04:45.200 --> 04:47.460
You're definitely in the right area there.

04:47.830 --> 04:50.630
I can feel a lot of energy
twisted up around there.

04:50.920 --> 04:52.540
Let me just see if I can...

05:02.300 --> 05:03.640
I went down.

05:03.720 --> 05:05.430
I didn't just get hurt, did I?

05:05.520 --> 05:07.140
It was worse than that.

05:07.230 --> 05:10.190
I was gone, but you brought me back.

05:10.730 --> 05:13.480
I just used the spirit water
from the North Pole.

05:13.560 --> 05:14.820
I don't know what I did, exactly.

05:15.860 --> 05:17.280
You saved me.

05:17.780 --> 05:19.200
You need to rest.

05:22.200 --> 05:26.950
WOMAN 1: Your Princess Azula,
clever and beautiful,

05:27.040 --> 05:32.670
disguised herself as the enemy
and entered the Earth Kingdom's capital.

05:32.750 --> 05:37.510
WOMAN 2: In Ba Sing Se,
she found her brother Zuko,

05:37.590 --> 05:40.470
and together, they faced the Avatar.

05:40.550 --> 05:46.310
BOTH WOMEN: And the Avatar fell,
and the Earth Kingdom fell.

05:46.390 --> 05:50.890
WOMAN 1: Azula's agents
quickly overtook the entire city.

05:51.270 --> 05:54.610
<i>They went to Ba Sing Se's great walls...</i>

05:54.690 --> 05:57.530
BOTH WOMEN: <i>...and brought them down.</i>

06:05.490 --> 06:09.500
WOMAN 2: The armies of the Fire Nation
surged through the wall

06:09.580 --> 06:15.380
and swarmed over Ba Sing Se,
securing our victory.

06:16.130 --> 06:17.750
( BABY CRYING )

06:27.010 --> 06:30.350
BOTH WOMEN: Now the heroes
have returned home.

06:30.430 --> 06:34.060
WOMAN 1: Your princess, Azula.

06:34.150 --> 06:37.320
( CHEERING AND APPLAUSE )

06:37.730 --> 06:42.700
And after three long years,
your prince has returned.

06:43.150 --> 06:44.490
Zuko.

06:45.740 --> 06:51.250
( CHEERING AND APPLAUSE )

06:53.500 --> 06:56.540
After what happened in Ba Sing Se,
we had to get you to safety.

06:57.590 --> 06:59.130
<i>We flew back to Chameleon Bay,</i>

06:59.210 --> 07:01.670
<i>where we found my father
and the other water tribe men.</i>

07:03.380 --> 07:06.340
<i>The Earth King decided he wanted
to travel the world in disguise,</i>

07:06.430 --> 07:07.760
<i>so he set off alone.</i>

07:07.850 --> 07:09.430
<i>Well, not completely alone.</i>

07:09.510 --> 07:10.680
( GROWLING )

07:13.810 --> 07:16.270
<i>Soon, the bay was overrun
with Fire Nation ships.</i>

07:16.350 --> 07:19.940
<i>Rather than fight them all, we captured
a single ship and made it our disguise.</i>

07:20.320 --> 07:22.320
Since then, we've been traveling west.

07:22.400 --> 07:24.490
We crossed through the Serpent's Pass
a few days ago.

07:25.030 --> 07:27.570
We've seen a few Fire Nation ships,
but none have bothered us.

07:28.660 --> 07:29.660
So, what now?

07:29.740 --> 07:32.790
We've been working on
a modified version of the invasion plan.

07:33.040 --> 07:35.410
It's Sokka's invasion plan.

07:36.120 --> 07:37.920
Yes, Sokka's plan.

07:38.670 --> 07:42.050
We won't be able to mount a massive
invasion without the Earth King's armies

07:42.130 --> 07:45.720
But the solar eclipse will still
leave the Fire Nation vulnerable.

07:46.130 --> 07:47.840
So we're planning a smaller invasion.

07:47.930 --> 07:51.010
Just a ragtag team of our friends
and allies from around the Earth Kingdom.

07:51.100 --> 07:53.180
We already ran into
Pipsqueak and The Duke.

07:53.810 --> 07:55.480
Good to see you again, Aang.

07:56.020 --> 07:59.560
And the best part is, the eclipse
isn't even our biggest advantage.

07:59.650 --> 08:01.900
We have a secret.

08:02.480 --> 08:04.240
- You.
- Me?

08:04.320 --> 08:06.610
Yep, the whole world thinks you're dead.

08:07.070 --> 08:08.700
Isn't that great?

08:13.370 --> 08:14.370
[ ♪... ]

08:14.910 --> 08:16.250
The world thinks I'm dead?

08:16.790 --> 08:18.210
How is that good news?

08:18.290 --> 08:19.290
That's terrible.

08:19.670 --> 08:20.710
No, it's great.

08:20.790 --> 08:23.000
It means the Fire Nation
won't be hunting us anymore.

08:23.210 --> 08:26.090
And even better, they won't be
expecting you on the day of black sun.

08:26.170 --> 08:27.720
No, no, no, no, no.

08:28.130 --> 08:29.680
You have no idea.

08:29.760 --> 08:31.220
This is so messed up.

08:31.470 --> 08:33.970
( HORN BLARING )

08:34.310 --> 08:35.930
I'll handle this.

08:36.020 --> 08:37.350
The Avatar is back.

08:37.440 --> 08:38.690
( GRUNTING )

08:39.190 --> 08:40.350
KATARA: Aang, wait.

08:40.440 --> 08:42.900
Remember, they don't know
we're not Fire Nation.

08:46.400 --> 08:48.530
Everyone, just stay calm.

08:48.610 --> 08:50.450
Bato and I will take care of this.

08:56.120 --> 08:58.660
I hate not being able to do anything.

08:58.750 --> 09:00.500
Hopefully, you won't need to.

09:13.050 --> 09:15.140
Commander, why are you off course?

09:15.510 --> 09:17.850
All western fleet ships
are supposed to be moving

09:17.930 --> 09:20.310
toward Ba Sing Se
to support the occupation.

09:20.730 --> 09:23.400
Actually, we're from the eastern fleet.

09:23.480 --> 09:25.150
We have orders to deliver some cargo.

09:25.480 --> 09:27.900
Ah, eastern fleet.

09:27.990 --> 09:31.910
Well, nice of Admiral Chan to let us know
he was sending one of his ships our way.

09:32.320 --> 09:34.950
I'm sure Admiral Chan
meant no disrespect, sir.

09:35.030 --> 09:38.330
I mean, how hard is it to write a quick
note and send a hawk our way?

09:39.000 --> 09:42.370
Next time, we'll send two hawks,
to be sure you get the message.

09:44.630 --> 09:48.090
Sir, Admiral Chan has been on leave
for two months at Ember Island.

09:48.170 --> 09:51.470
What? Why doesn't anyone
ever tell me anything?

09:51.550 --> 09:52.760
Something's not right.

09:52.840 --> 09:54.010
They should've known that.

09:54.100 --> 09:55.470
I think this is a captured ship.

09:56.680 --> 09:58.930
Just stay quiet
until we're safely across the ramp.

09:59.390 --> 10:01.390
Then we'll sink this ship.

10:02.480 --> 10:03.520
They know!

10:06.110 --> 10:07.400
( GRUNTING )

10:08.570 --> 10:10.240
( SCREAMING )

10:14.820 --> 10:15.830
( GRUNTING )

10:36.470 --> 10:37.890
( QUACKING )

10:37.970 --> 10:39.390
You seem so downcast.

10:39.640 --> 10:41.520
Has Mai gotten to you already?

10:41.600 --> 10:44.770
Though actually, Mai has been
in a strangely good mood lately.

10:45.350 --> 10:46.940
I haven't seen dad yet.

10:47.020 --> 10:50.360
I haven't seen him in three years,
since I was banished.

10:50.440 --> 10:51.690
AZULA: So what?

10:51.780 --> 10:54.030
So, I didn't capture the Avatar.

10:54.530 --> 10:56.910
Who cares? The Avatar's dead.

10:58.990 --> 11:03.250
Unless you think he somehow
miraculously survived.

11:05.370 --> 11:08.000
KATARA: This is water from
the spirit oasis at the North Pole.

11:08.290 --> 11:12.260
It has special properties, so I've been
saving it for something important.

11:13.630 --> 11:14.970
No.

11:15.050 --> 11:17.010
There's no way he could've survived.

11:21.850 --> 11:25.230
Well, then I'm sure you have
nothing to worry about.

11:40.240 --> 11:41.790
Load the Toph!

11:41.870 --> 11:43.370
( GRUNTING )

12:21.870 --> 12:23.240
I'm gonna give us some cover.

12:45.270 --> 12:47.850
I can't just stand by and do nothing.

12:47.940 --> 12:49.060
Aang, no!

12:49.770 --> 12:52.520
You're still hurt,
and you have to stay secret.

12:52.610 --> 12:54.320
Just let us handle this.

12:55.030 --> 12:56.110
Fine.

13:07.450 --> 13:08.580
TOPH: How we doing?

13:08.660 --> 13:10.000
Things couldn't get much worse.

13:10.080 --> 13:12.290
( DRAGON GROWLING )

13:13.590 --> 13:16.840
The universe just loves
proving me wrong, doesn't it?

13:16.920 --> 13:18.300
You make it too easy.

13:31.850 --> 13:33.770
Thank you, the universe.

13:44.660 --> 13:45.950
Hey, Aang.

13:46.040 --> 13:47.750
We're going into town to find some dinner.

13:48.250 --> 13:49.460
( STOMACH GRUMBLING )

13:49.540 --> 13:51.580
Well, I am pretty hungry.

13:51.670 --> 13:53.170
Maybe dinner's a good idea.

13:53.960 --> 13:55.380
Here, tie this around your head.

13:55.460 --> 13:56.800
It'll cover your arrow.

13:57.250 --> 14:00.090
I'm not going out
if I can't wear my arrow proudly.

14:00.630 --> 14:01.630
Aang, come on.

14:01.720 --> 14:02.720
Be practical.

14:03.470 --> 14:04.850
You guys go ahead without us.

14:04.930 --> 14:06.220
We'll catch up with you.

14:08.770 --> 14:12.440
I think I understand why
being a secret bothers you so much.

14:12.520 --> 14:14.400
You don't want people to think you failed.

14:14.480 --> 14:15.770
You're right, I don't.

14:15.860 --> 14:18.150
But the problem is, I did fail.

14:18.570 --> 14:20.400
Aang, that's not true.

14:20.490 --> 14:21.990
It is true.

14:22.070 --> 14:23.530
I was in Ba Sing Se.

14:23.610 --> 14:26.620
I was there, but I lost.

14:27.200 --> 14:29.290
And now, the Earth Kingdom
has fallen for good.

14:30.000 --> 14:31.410
It's not for good.

14:31.500 --> 14:33.040
Remember, there's still a plan.

14:33.120 --> 14:34.290
The invasion.

14:34.380 --> 14:36.420
And I hate the invasion plan, too.

14:36.500 --> 14:40.510
I don't want you or anyone else
risking your lives to fix my mistakes.

14:41.260 --> 14:44.050
I've always known
that I would have to face the Fire Lord

14:44.130 --> 14:45.840
But now I know I need to do it alone.

14:46.640 --> 14:47.970
Aang.

14:48.060 --> 14:49.220
Katara, please.

14:49.770 --> 14:52.100
Just go, please.

14:54.190 --> 14:55.850
Is there anything you need?

14:57.650 --> 14:59.150
I need to redeem myself.

14:59.940 --> 15:01.900
I need my honor back.

15:12.750 --> 15:15.250
( SIGHING )

15:28.930 --> 15:30.260
I brought you some food.

15:33.180 --> 15:34.390
Oh, no.

15:50.410 --> 15:53.120
You have been away for a long time.

15:53.660 --> 15:56.460
I see the weight of your travels
has changed you.

15:57.000 --> 16:00.250
You have redeemed yourself, my son.

16:05.470 --> 16:07.180
Welcome home.

16:12.600 --> 16:13.970
[ ♪... ]

16:27.450 --> 16:29.410
I'll leave you two alone.

16:30.870 --> 16:32.200
What's wrong, Katara?

16:32.280 --> 16:33.450
He left.

16:33.540 --> 16:34.540
What?

16:34.620 --> 16:35.620
Aang.

16:35.700 --> 16:37.830
He just took his glider and disappeared.

16:37.920 --> 16:41.960
He has this ridiculous notion
that he has to save the world alone

16:42.040 --> 16:43.710
That it's all his responsibility.

16:44.250 --> 16:46.420
Maybe that's his way of being brave.

16:46.510 --> 16:49.300
It's not brave. It's selfish and stupid.

16:49.380 --> 16:52.180
We could be helping him,
and I know the world needs him,

16:52.260 --> 16:54.890
but doesn't he know how much
that we need him too?

16:54.970 --> 16:56.520
How could he just leave us behind?

16:58.390 --> 17:00.690
You're talking about me too, aren't you?

17:01.060 --> 17:03.480
How could you leave us, dad?

17:03.570 --> 17:07.030
I mean, I know we had Gran-Gran,
and she loved us, but...

17:07.110 --> 17:09.700
But we were just so lost without you.

17:10.160 --> 17:11.530
( SOBBING )

17:11.620 --> 17:13.240
I'm so sorry, Katara.

17:16.040 --> 17:18.160
I understand why you left.

17:18.250 --> 17:22.210
I really do,
and I know that you had to go,

17:22.290 --> 17:25.880
so why do I still feel this way?

17:25.960 --> 17:29.970
I was so sad and angry, and hurt.

17:30.300 --> 17:33.100
I love you more than anything.

17:33.180 --> 17:35.680
You and your brother are my entire world.

17:36.100 --> 17:40.810
I thought about you every day I was gone,
and every night when I went to sleep

17:40.890 --> 17:44.980
I would lie awake
missing you so much it would ache.

17:48.530 --> 17:51.110
OZAI: I am proud of you, Prince Zuko.

17:51.200 --> 17:55.200
I am proud because you
and your sister conquered Ba Sing Se.

17:55.580 --> 18:00.870
I am proud because when your loyalty
was tested by your treacherous uncle

18:00.960 --> 18:04.500
you did the right thing
and captured the traitor

18:04.840 --> 18:09.420
And I am proudest of all
of your most legendary accomplishment.

18:09.760 --> 18:12.340
You slayed the Avatar.

18:13.180 --> 18:14.340
What did you hear?

18:14.430 --> 18:16.050
Azula told me everything.

18:17.010 --> 18:19.020
She said she was amazed and impressed

18:19.100 --> 18:24.150
with your power and ferocity
at the moment of truth.

18:31.280 --> 18:32.780
AANG: Blockade.

18:35.240 --> 18:36.410
( INHALING )

18:46.380 --> 18:47.880
( GASPING )

18:57.220 --> 18:58.470
( GRUNTING )

19:15.780 --> 19:16.870
( GRUNTING )

19:21.700 --> 19:22.790
ZUKO: Why'd you do it?

19:24.330 --> 19:26.960
You're going to have to be
a little more specific.

19:27.500 --> 19:30.710
Why did you tell father
that I was the one who killed the Avatar?

19:30.800 --> 19:32.710
AZULA: Can't this wait until morning?

19:33.050 --> 19:34.300
It can't.

19:34.840 --> 19:36.470
( SIGHING ) Fine.

19:37.550 --> 19:40.060
You seemed so worried
about how father would treat you

19:40.140 --> 19:42.430
because you hadn't captured the Avatar.

19:42.520 --> 19:45.730
I figured, if I gave you the credit,
you'd have nothing to worry about.

19:45.810 --> 19:46.810
But why?

19:46.900 --> 19:49.190
Call it a generous gesture.

19:49.270 --> 19:53.280
I wanted to thank you for your help,
and I was happy to share the glory.

19:53.530 --> 19:54.780
You're lying.

19:55.570 --> 19:56.820
If you say so.

19:57.490 --> 19:59.280
You have another motive for doing this.

19:59.370 --> 20:01.370
I just haven't figured out what it is.

20:01.450 --> 20:02.700
Please, Zuko.

20:03.080 --> 20:05.290
What ulterior motive could I have?

20:05.370 --> 20:07.080
What could I possibly gain

20:07.170 --> 20:10.500
by letting you get all the glory
for defeating the Avatar?

20:10.750 --> 20:14.510
Unless, somehow,
the Avatar was actually alive.

20:15.340 --> 20:19.590
All that glory would suddenly
turn to shame and foolishness.

20:21.180 --> 20:24.980
But you said yourself,
that was impossible.

20:25.890 --> 20:27.520
Sleep well, Zu Zu.

20:38.860 --> 20:41.620
( SCREAMING )

20:48.250 --> 20:50.290
( GASPING )

20:53.130 --> 20:55.340
I'm not gonna make it.

20:55.420 --> 20:56.420
I failed.

20:56.510 --> 20:58.680
( THUNDER RUMBLING )

20:58.760 --> 21:00.050
Roku?

21:00.140 --> 21:02.220
You haven't failed, Aang.

21:02.930 --> 21:04.970
But everyone thinks I'm dead again.

21:05.520 --> 21:09.770
They think I've abandoned them,
and I'm losing this war.

21:09.850 --> 21:11.810
I'm letting the whole world down.

21:12.150 --> 21:16.900
ROKU: If anyone is to blame
for the state of the world, it is me.

21:16.990 --> 21:20.110
I should've seen this war coming,
and prevented it.

21:20.740 --> 21:25.200
You inherited my problems and my mistakes

21:25.290 --> 21:30.500
But I believe you are destined
to redeem me, and save the world.

21:30.870 --> 21:32.170
I don't know.

21:33.170 --> 21:35.300
YUE: You already saved the world.

21:38.420 --> 21:40.470
And you'll save the world again.

21:40.760 --> 21:42.890
But you can't give up.

21:47.680 --> 21:48.770
You're right.

21:49.180 --> 21:50.690
I won't give up.

22:29.310 --> 22:31.350
( CHIRPING )

22:34.020 --> 22:36.270
( GROANING )

22:40.440 --> 22:41.820
You're ok.

22:46.280 --> 22:48.660
( GROWLING )

22:51.250 --> 22:52.830
I have so much to do.

22:52.910 --> 22:54.960
I know, but you'll have our help.

22:55.040 --> 22:56.840
You didn't think
you could get out of training

22:56.920 --> 22:58.840
just by coming to the Fire Nation,
did you?

23:00.510 --> 23:02.050
What about the invasion?

23:02.130 --> 23:05.510
We'll join up with my dad and the invasion
force on the day of the eclipse.

23:05.590 --> 23:07.100
Hey, what's...

23:08.050 --> 23:10.810
Oh, it's your glider.

23:11.560 --> 23:12.850
That's ok.

23:14.690 --> 23:17.770
If someone saw it,
it would give away my identity.

23:18.230 --> 23:20.820
It's better for now
that no one knows I'm alive.

23:48.550 --> 23:50.010
[ ♪... ]
